# 🎯 Main Objective: Update the Changelog

- [ ] 1. Create version header
  - [ ] 1.1. Add semantic version with date
    ```markdown
    ## 🚀 Version 1.2.3 (January 2024)
    ---
    ```
  - [ ] 1.2. Verify version follows semantic versioning (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH)

- [ ] 2. Add change sections
  - [ ] 2.1. Create breaking changes section if needed
    ```markdown
    ### 💔 Breaking:
    * Removed deprecated `oldMethod` - use `newMethod` instead
    ```
  - [ ] 2.2. Create features section
    ```markdown
    ### ✨ Features:
    * Added `newFeature` to handle X functionality
    ```
  - [ ] 2.3. Create improvements section
    ```markdown
    ### 🛠️ Improvements:
    * Updated `existingFeature` to improve performance
    ```
  - [ ] 2.4. Create bug fixes section
    ```markdown
    ### 🐛 Bug fixes:
    * Fixed crash in `brokenFeature` when input was null
    ```

- [ ] 3. Document changes
  - [ ] 3.1. Start each bullet with action verb
  - [ ] 3.2. Wrap code references in backticks
  - [ ] 3.3. Reference issue numbers if applicable
    ```markdown
    * Added `newFeature` to handle X functionality (#123)
    ```

- [ ] 4. Validate changelog
  - [ ] 4.1. Verify sections are in correct order (Breaking → Features → Improvements → Fixes)
  - [ ] 4.2. Check all code references use backticks
  - [ ] 4.3. Confirm bullet points are clear and concise
